brief_description of the content in the: The source URL provides information about a rule that reports illegal method names passed to the 'dependsOnMethods' attribute in the @Test annotation in Java-TestNG. An illegal method name is one that cannot be resolved into a valid, accessible @Test annotated method in the current class or any of its parent classes.
generated_rule_explanation from GPT-4: The rule 'illegal-method-name-dependsOnMethods' checks all classes and their methods. If a method has the @Test annotation, it retrieves the 'dependsOnMethods' attribute. For each method name in 'dependsOnMethods', it asserts that there exists a method in the same class with the same name and the @Test annotation. If the assertion fails, it generates a message indicating the illegal method name, the method where it was found, and the class containing the method.
